      • isVersionGreaterThanOrEqualTo

        public static boolean isVersionGreaterThanOrEqualTo(String version)
                                             throws FedoraClientException

        Returns true if the server version (provided by FedoraClient.getServerVersion()) is greater than or equal to the supplied version.

        Note that 3.6 is greater than 3.6-SNAPSHOT and 2.12 is greater than 2.2.

        Parameters:
        version - The version to compare against (e.g. 3.5 or 3.6-SNAPSHOT)
        Returns:
        true if the server-provided version is greater than or equal to the supplied version
        Throws:
        FedoraClientException
